<div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always; WIDTH: 100%">
<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: center; WIDTH: 100%"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">21</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: center; WIDTH: 100%">
<hr style="COLOR: black" noshade size="2">
</div>
</div>

<div id="HDR">
<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">&#160; </font></div>
</div>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Item 1A. Risk Factors</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: -1pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Risks Related to our Operations (Continued)</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">L. We are subject to many forms of environmental regulation and may incur substantial costs as a result.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">We are also subject to increasingly stringent federal, state, and local laws, regulations and ordinances relating to the protection of the environment, including those relating to emissions in the air. Compliance with all environmental laws and regulations can require significant expenditures.&#160;&#160;There is increasing regulatory focus in North America on climate change and greenhouse gas emissions.&#160;&#160;While we cannot yet determine what the final regulatory programs will be in the United States or in other areas in which we do business, such climate change-related regulatory activity in the future may adversely affect our business and financial results.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Risks Related to our Labor Costs and Collective Bargaining Agreements</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: -1pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">M. Increases in our labor costs, which constitute a substantial portion of our total operating costs, may directly affect our earnings.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: -1pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Labor costs are not directly reimbursed by any of our code-share partners.&#160;&#160;Rather, compensation for these costs is intended to be covered by the payments based on pre-set rates for block hours, departures, and fixed costs.&#160;&#160;Labor costs constitute a significant portion, ranging from 31% to 33%, of our total operating costs.&#160;&#160;Pressure to increase these costs beyond standard industry wages, and therefore beyond the limits intended to be covered by the fixed payments we receive from our code-share partners, is increased by the high degree of unionization of our workforce.&#160;&#160;As of December 31, 2010, 73% of our employees were unionized.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: -1pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Additionally, on February 17, 2011, we entered into a new agreement with ALPA, the union representing pilots at Pinnacle, Mesaba, and Colgan.&#160;&#160;The joint agreement represents an amendment to the collective bargaining agreements at Pinnacle and Mesaba, and a first agreement with Colgan&#8217;s pilots.&#160;&#160;The terms of the agreement will materially increase our pilots&#8217; salaries, wages, and benefits costs.&#160;&#160;The agreement contains increased pay rates for pilots at Pinnacle and Colgan, as well as a material signing bonus for Pinnacle&#8217;s pilots.&#160;&#160;An increase in our labor costs over standard industry wages could result in a material reduction to our earnings, and could affect our future prospects for additional business opportunities.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: -1pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">N. Strikes or labor disputes with our employees may adversely affect our ability to conduct our business and could result in the termination, or a significant reduction of the benefit, of our code-share agreements.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: -1pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">If we are unable to reach collective bargaining agreements upon their initial or amendable dates with any of our unionized work groups in accordance with the Railway Labor Act, we may be subject to work interruptions, work stoppages, or a fleet size reduction.&#160;&#160;Work stoppages may adversely affect our ability to conduct our operations and fulfill our obligations under our code-share agreements.&#160;&#160;&#160;Several of our code-share agreements contain provisions granting our partners the right to terminate our agreements in the event of a work stoppage or labor strike.&#160;&#160;Additionally, our CRJ-200 ASA contains a provision allowing Delta to reduce the size of our CRJ-200 fleet in the event of a work stoppage or labor strike.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">O.&#160;&#160;If we are unable to attract and retain key employees, our business could be harmed.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">We compete against the other major and regional U.S. airlines for pilots, mechanics, and other employee groups essential for providing airlines services.&#160; Several of the other airlines offer wage and benefit packages that exceed ours.&#160; We may be required to increase wages and/or benefits in order to attract and retain qualified employees or risk considerable turnover, which could negatively affect our ability to provide a quality product to our customers and therefore negatively affect our relationship with our customers.&#160;</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Similarly, as we further expand our Q400 operations for United, our need increases for qualified pilots, mechanics, and other airline-specific employees.&#160; If we are unable to hire, train, and retain qualified pilots we would be unable to efficiently run our operations and our competitive ability would be impaired.&#160; Our business could be harmed and revenue reduced if, due to a shortage of pilots, we are forced to cancel flights and forego earning incentive-based revenue under our code-share agreements.</font></div>

<br>
<div id="PGBRK" style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; WIDTH: 100%; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
<div id="FTR">
<div style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">

</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold"><a name="Item1B">Item 1B.&#160;&#160;Unresolved Staff Comments</a></font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 36pt"></font>All staff comments received from the SEC were resolved as of the date of this filing.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold"><a name="Item2">Item 2.&#160;</a>&#160;<a name="Item2properties">Properties</a></font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold"><a name="Item2facilities">Facilities</a></font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div id="HDR">
<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">&#160; </font></div>
</div>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Item 2.&#160;&#160;Properties</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Facilities (Continued)</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Our significant maintenance facilities are located in cities that we serve based on market size, frequency, and location.&#160;&#160;These facilities are used for overnight maintenance; however, Memphis, Dulles, and Wausau are also used during the day.&#160;&#160;We have additional smaller maintenance facilities in Atlanta, Georgia; New York City, New York (John F. Kennedy); Salt Lake City, Utah; Fort Wayne, Indiana; and Austin, Texas.&#160;&#160;While the facilities are highly utilized with an average turn around time of seven to ten hours, we believe that our existing facilities are adequate for the foreseeable needs of our current and growing business.&#160;&#160;As our fleet grows, we may seek additional maintenance space in the future.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">In connection with our code-share agreements, we maintain contract service agreements with Delta, United, and US Airways allowing for the use of terminal gates, parking positions, and operations space at airports in Atlanta, Boston, Detroit, Houston, Memphis, Minneapolis/St. Paul, Newark, New York City, and Washington-Dulles, as well as most of the stations we serve from these hub airports.&#160;&#160;We believe the use of the terminal gates, parking positions, and operations space obtained from our code-share partners will be sufficient to meet the operational needs of our business.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">In December 2010, we entered into a 13-year lease whereby we will occupy 170,000 square feet of the One Commerce Square building in downtown Memphis.&#160;&#160;We intend to vacate our existing headquarters facilities in Memphis in the fall of 2011 and begin occupying this space.&#160;&#160;Ultimately, we expect to relocate Mesaba&#8217;s headquarters to this space as well.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold"><a name="Item3">Item 3.</a>&#160;<a name="Item3legalproceedings">&#160;Legal Proceedings</a></font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">We are subject to certain legal actions that occur in the ordinary course of our business. While the outcome of these actions cannot be predicted with certainty, it is the opinion of our management, based on current information and legal advice, that the ultimate disposition of these actions will not have a material adverse effect on our consolidated financial statements as a whole.&#160;&#160;For further discussion, see Note 16, <font style="FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">Commitments and Contingencies</font>, in Item 8 of this Form 10-K.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><font style="FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">September 11, 2001 Litigation.&#160;&#160;</font>Colgan is a defendant in litigation resulting from the September 11, 2001 terrorist attacks.&#160;&#160;We believe we will prevail in this litigation; moreover, we believe that any adverse outcome from this litigation would be covered by insurance and would therefore have no material adverse effect on our financial position, results of operations, and cash flows.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><font style="FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">Colgan&#160;Flight 3407</font>.&#160;&#160;On February 12, 2009, Colgan Flight 3407, operated under the Company&#8217;s United Q400 CPA, crashed in a neighborhood near the Buffalo Niagara International Airport in Buffalo, New York. All 49 people aboard, including 45 passengers and four members of the flight crew, died in the accident. Additionally, one individual died inside the home destroyed by the aircraft&#8217;s impact.&#160;&#160;Several lawsuits related to this accident have been filed against the Company, and additional litigation is anticipated.&#160;&#160;We carry aviation liability insurance and believe that this insurance is sufficient to cover any liability arising from this accident.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold"><a name="Item3environmental">Environmental Matters</a></font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">We are subject to regulation under various environmental laws and regulations, which are administered by numerous state and federal agencies. In addition, many state and local governments have adopted environmental laws and regulations to which our operations are subject. We are, and may from time to time become, involved in environmental matters, including the investigation and/or remediation of environmental conditions at properties used or previously used by us. We are not, however, currently subject to any environmental cleanup orders imposed by regulatory authorities, nor do we have any active investigations or remediation at this time.</font></div>

<br>
<div id="PGBRK" style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; WIDTH: 100%; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
<div id="FTR">
<div style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block">&#160;</div>
</div>

<div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">&#160; </font></div>

</div>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Item 3.&#160;&#160;Legal Proceedings</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold"><a name="Item3regulatorymatters">Regulatory Matters</a></font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">We are subject to regulation under various laws and regulations which are administered by numerous state and federal agencies, including but not limited to the FAA, the DOT, and the TSA.&#160;&#160;We are involved in various matters with these agencies during the ordinary course of our business.&#160;&#160;While the outcome of these matters cannot be predicted with certainty, it is the opinion of our management, based on current information and past experience, that the ultimate disposition of these matters will not have a material adverse effect on our financial condition as a whole.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block">&#160;</div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: center; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Part II</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold"><a name="Item5">Item 5.&#160; Market for Registrant&#8217;s Common Equity, Related Stockholder Matters and Issuer Purchases of Equity Securities</a></font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>

Set forth below, for the applicable periods indicated, are the high and low closing sale prices per share of our common stock as reported by the Nasdaq Global Select Market.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">As of February 21, 2011, there were approximately 32 holders of record of our common stock.&#160;&#160;We have paid no cash dividends on our common stock and have no current intention of doing so in the future.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">The information under the caption &#8220;Securities Authorized for Issuance under Equity Compensation Plans,&#8221; appearing in the Proxy Statement for our 2011 Annual Meeting of Stockholders, to be filed with the Commission within the 120 days after December 31, 2010, is hereby incorporated by reference.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Our Certificate of Incorporation provides that no shares of capital stock may be voted by or at the direction of persons who are not United States citizens unless such shares are registered on a separate stock record. Our Bylaws further provide that no shares will be registered on such separate stock record if the amount so registered would exceed United States foreign ownership restrictions. United States law currently limits to 25% the voting power in our company (or any other U.S. airline) of persons who are not citizens of the United States.</font></div>

<br>
<div id="PGBRK" style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; WIDTH: 100%; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
<div id="FTR">
<div style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">

</div>

<div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">&#160; </font></div>

<tr>
<td valign="top" width="5%" style="TEXT-ALIGN: right">
<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: right; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">(1)&#160; </font></div>
</td>
<td valign="top" width="78%">
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">The balance sheet was affected by the July 1, 2010 acquisition of Mesaba and the January 18, 2007 acquisition of Colgan.</font></div>
</td>
</tr><tr>
<td valign="top" width="5%" style="TEXT-ALIGN: right">
<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: right; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">(2)&#160; </font></div>
</td>
<td valign="top" width="78%">
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">For the year ended December 31, 2010 and 2009, total assets include approximately $275 million and $300 million, respectively on long-term receivables related to potential claims related to Colgan Flight 3407. This amount is offset in its entirety by a corresponding liability.&#160;&#160;For more information, see Note 16, <font style="FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">Commitments and Contingencies</font>, in Item 8 of this Form 10-K.</font></div>
</td>
</tr><tr>
<td valign="top" width="5%" style="TEXT-ALIGN: right">
<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: right; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">(3)&#160; </font></div>
</td>
<td valign="top" width="78%">
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">For the year ended December 31, 2006, cash and cash equivalents did not include the recurring CRJ-200 ASA end-of-month payment of $31.9 million, which was received on January 2, 2007 as December 31, 2006 was not a business day.</font></div>
</td>
</tr></table>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%" style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">
<tr>
<td valign="top" width="5%" style="TEXT-ALIGN: right">
<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: right; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">(1)&#160; </font></div>
</td>
<td valign="top" width="78%">
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">We acquired Mesaba on July 1, 2010.&#160;&#160;Data for 2010 includes Mesaba data and statistics from the date of acquisition through the end of the year.&#160;&#160;We acquired Colgan on January 18, 2007.&#160;&#160;Data for 2007 includes Colgan data and statistics&#160;from the date of acquisition through the end of the year.</font></div>
</td>
</tr><tr>
<td valign="top" width="5%" style="TEXT-ALIGN: right">
<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: right; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">(2)&#160; </font></div>
</td>
<td valign="top" width="78%">
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">Revenue passenger miles represent the number of miles flown by revenue passengers.</font></div>
</td>
</tr><tr>
<td valign="top" width="5%" style="TEXT-ALIGN: right">
<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: right; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">(3)&#160; </font></div>
</td>
<td valign="top" width="78%">
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">Available seat miles represent the number of seats available for passengers multiplied by the number of miles the seats are flown.</font></div>
</td>
</tr><tr>
<td valign="top" width="5%" style="TEXT-ALIGN: right">
<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: right; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">(4)&#160; </font></div>
</td>
<td valign="top" width="78%">
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">Passenger load factor equals revenue passenger miles divided by available seat miles.</font></div>
</td>
</tr></table>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left">&#160;</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Item 6.&#160;&#160;Selected Financial Data </font><br>
</div>

<td align="left" valign="bottom" width="40%">
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: -18pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Provision for decreases in losses associated with bankruptcy filings</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: -18pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; &#160;of Northwest and Mesaba</font></div>

<div id="HDR">
<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">&#160; </font></div>

<div style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold"><a name="Item7">Item 7.&#160;&#160;Management&#8217;s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations</a></font></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<br>
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold"><a name="Item7overviewandoutlook">Overview and Outlook</a></font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 36pt"></font>2010 Results</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Our consolidated operating income decreased by $19.2 million in 2010 as compared to 2009.&#160;&#160;Pinnacle experienced a decline in operating income of $10.6 million, primarily attributable to a one-time charge of $10.9 million related to a signing bonus contained in an agreement with ALPA, as more fully discussed below.&#160;&#160;Colgan&#8217;s operating income decreased by $15.4 million.&#160;&#160;The large decline was primarily related to substantially higher maintenance costs on our Saab and Q400 fleets, higher pilot and flight attendant wages due to an increase in employees prior to the launch of new Q400 service in late 2010, and higher fuel costs in our pro-rate operations.&#160;&#160;These significant cost increases were partially offset by a 9% increase in revenue per available seat mile within our pro-rate operations.&#
160;&#160;Mesaba earned $6.8 million in operating income during the six months ended December 31, 2010.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Mesaba Acquisition</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">On July 1, 2010, we purchased Mesaba from Delta for total consideration of $75 million.&#160;&#160;Mesaba operates a fleet of 41 CRJ-900 aircraft, 19 CRJ-200 aircraft, and 26 Saab 340B+ aircraft as a Delta Connection carrier, with hubs in Atlanta, Detroit, Memphis, Minneapolis/St. Paul, and Salt Lake City.&#160;&#160;All of Mesaba&#8217;s aircraft are leased from Delta under contracts conterminous with their respective operating agreements with Delta.&#160;&#160;In connection with our acquisition of Mesaba, we entered into a new capacity purchase agreement with Delta providing for the operation of Mesaba&#8217;s CRJ-900 fleet for a period of 12 years (the &#8220;Mesaba CRJ-900 DCA&#8221;), and we modified our existing CRJ-200 airline services agreement (the &#8220;CRJ-200 ASA&#8221;) with Delta to include Mesaba&#8217;s fleet of CRJ-2
00 aircraft.&#160;&#160;We also entered into a two-year capacity purchase agreement covering Mesaba&#8217;s fleet of 26 Saab 340 B+ aircraft (the &#8220;Saab DCA&#8221;).&#160;&#160;Under these agreements, Delta will pay us rates and reimburse us certain direct expenses, similar to our existing capacity purchase agreements with Delta.&#160;&#160;These agreements provide for targeted cash income (cash payments received from Delta less all expenses other than depreciation and amortization and interest expense, and less forecasted capital expenditures) of $18 million per year through July 2022.&#160;&#160;Because these agreements contain rates that increase annually with inflation, we can earn more or less than $18 million of cash contract income in any given year depending on how our expenses fluctuate.&#160;&#160;&#160;In addition, primarily because depreciation and amortization are generally excluded from reimbursement under these agreements, our reported operating income under generally accepted accounting 
principles related to Mesaba&#8217;s operations will differ from the $18 million target cash contract income.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">These agreements also provide for certain rate resets.&#160;&#160;Under these rate resets, we will negotiate and agree with Delta on new rates based on a forecast of our projected cash expenditures under the agreements for the subsequent five-year period, inclusive of our targeted cash contract income of $18 million per year.&#160;&#160;Finally, these agreements contain targets related to our operating performance, and we can earn additional incentives or incur performance penalties depending on our actual operating performance.&#160;&#160;Because we will incur some integration costs during 2011 and 2012, we do not expect to realize the full $18 million targeted cash contract income during these years.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Prior to selling Mesaba to us, Delta announced plans to retire Mesaba&#8217;s fleet of Saab 340B+ aircraft during 2011.&#160;&#160;Accordingly, the Saab DCA provides for the wind-down of Mesaba&#8217;s Saab 340B+ operations over a period not to extend beyond June 2012.&#160;&#160;Under the Saab DCA, we do not expect to earn a material amount of income or incur a material loss while we operate the Saab 340B+ aircraft.&#160;&#160;As each aircraft exits service, we will return the aircraft to Delta on an &#8220;as is, where is&#8221; basis.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 36pt"></font>Simultaneously with our acquisition of Mesaba, we resolved certain contractual disputes relating to our existing capacity purchase agreements with Delta resulting in no gains or losses recognized and greater stability in our future cash flows under these contracts.&#160;&#160;For additional information about these disputes, refer to Note 3, <font style="FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">Code-Share Agreements with Partners, </font>and Note 4, <font style="FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">Acquisition of Mesaba,</font> to our consolidated financial statements, which are included in Item 8 of this Form 10-K.</font></div>

<br>
<div id="PGBRK" style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; WIDTH: 100%; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
<div id="FTR">
<div style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">&#160;</div>

<div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">&#160; </font></div>
</div>

<div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always; WIDTH: 100%">
<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: center; WIDTH: 100%"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">30</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: center; WIDTH: 100%">
<hr style="COLOR: black" noshade size="2">
</div>
</div>

<div id="HDR">
<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">&#160; </font></div>

<div style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Item 7.&#160;&#160;Management&#8217;s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations </font></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<br>
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Overview and Outlook (Continued)</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">ALPA Collective Bargaining Agreement</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">We had been in negotiations with ALPA to amend the collective bargaining agreement covering Pinnacle&#8217;s Pilots since April 2005, and we had been negotiating with ALPA to establish an initial collective bargaining agreement applicable to Colgan&#8217;s Pilots since late 2009.&#160;&#160;Upon the acquisition of Mesaba, we agreed with ALPA to negotiate for a new combined collective bargaining agreement covering the pilots at all three of our subsidiaries, and in December 2010 we reached a tentative agreement.&#160;&#160;The tentative agreement contains substantial salary and benefits increases for our pilots, bringing their total compensation in line with the average for airlines with similarly sized aircraft.&#160;&#160;The tentative agreement also contains a one-time $10.9 million signing bonus that will be paid to pilots at Pinna
cle Airlines.&#160;&#160;We accrued this one-time bonus in the fourth quarter of 2010.&#160;&#160;Pilots at all three airlines ratified the contract in February 2011, and the provisions will go into effect immediately.&#160;&#160;Exclusive of the one-time signing bonus, we expect our total pilot costs to increase by approximately $18 million during 2011 as a result of the new agreement.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">In connection with our acquisition of Mesaba, we modified our existing capacity purchase agreements with Delta to provide for a rate adjustment that will be effective upon the earlier of the date that we implement a combined collective bargaining agreement covering both Pinnacle&#8217;s and Mesaba&#8217;s pilots, or the date that the jet operations of Pinnacle and Mesaba are combined under a single operating certificate the (&#8220;Adjustment Trigger Date&#8221;).&#160;&#160;This rate adjustment is designed to increase Pinnacle&#8217;s rates commensurate with the increase in pilot labor costs related to Pinnacle&#8217;s Delta operations.&#160;&#160;The rate adjustment will be calculated and agreed to by us and Delta 12 months after the Adjustment Trigger Date.&#160;&#160;At that time, we will receive a one-time retroactive adjustment 
related to the prior 12 months for the increase in our pilot costs, inclusive of training and displacement related to the merging of Pinnacle&#8217;s and Mesaba&#8217;s pilot groups.&#160;&#160;In addition, we will receive a prospective adjustment payable for future periods such that our rates pertaining to pilot costs will be approximately equivalent to our actual pilot costs at the time of the rate adjustment.&#160;&#160;We believe that the Adjustment Trigger Date will occur upon the implementation of our new agreement with ALPA in March 2011.&#160;&#160;While we will not receive any cash payments related to these adjustments from Delta until 2012, we currently estimate that the one-time retroactive adjustment related to the 12 months ended March 2012 could be as much as $20 million, and the prospective rate increase that would begin in March 2012 could be as much as $14 million annually.&#160;&#160;These rate adjustments will be based on assumptions about cost allocations between the pilot groups of our o
perating subsidiaries, and will be subject to negotiation with Delta.&#160;&#160;No assurances can be made that the amount of the rate adjustments ultimately agreed to with Delta will equal our current estimates.&#160;&#160;While we are still evaluating the timing of revenue recognition associated with these adjustments, we currently believe that we will not recognize this revenue until 2012 upon the final determination of the amount.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;In addition, with the exception of annual increases indexed to the Producer Price Index, the rates associated with our pilot labor costs under all of our CPAs with Delta will not be adjusted again until 2018.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Operational Integration Plan</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Upon acquiring Mesaba, we announced that our long-term plan for our operating structure is to transition all jet flying to Pinnacle, and to merge Colgan and Mesaba&#8217;s turboprop operations with Mesaba remaining the surviving carrier.&#160;&#160;We aspire for our regional airline subsidiaries to lead the industry with regard to safety programs and a strong safety culture, and our realignment of operations will be implemented with this goal as our highest priority.&#160;&#160;We believe that realigning the common fleet types of Pinnacle, Mesaba and Colgan into two strong regional airlines also will provide for the most efficient and reliable regional operations for our partners.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Since the acquisition, we have completed the plan to integrate the jet operations of Pinnacle and Mesaba, and to merge Colgan&#8217;s and Mesaba&#8217;s turboprop operations.&#160;&#160;Implementation of our integration plan is subject to FAA approval, which we expect to obtain during the first half of 2011.&#160;&#160;We currently anticipate that completion of our integration will take 12 to 18 months after approval by the FAA.&#160;&#160;Our implementation plan will include significant one-time costs associated with training, relocation and displacement for our pilots, flight attendants and mechanics, information technology costs related to the integration of systems and operating processes, and relocation, retention and severance packages for management employees as we combine administrative functions.&#160;&#160;We currently est
imate that these one-time integration costs will be approximately $12 to $14 million, the majority of which we expect to incur during 2011.&#160;&#160;An insignificant amount of integration costs were incurred in 2010.</font></div>

<br>
<div id="PGBRK" style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; WIDTH: 100%; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
<div id="FTR">
<div style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block">&#160;</div>
</div>

<div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">&#160; </font></div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: center; WIDTH: 100%"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">31</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: center; WIDTH: 100%">
<hr style="COLOR: black" noshade size="2">
</div>
</div>

<div id="HDR">
<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">&#160; </font></div>

<div style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Item 7.&#160;&#160;Management&#8217;s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations </font></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<br>
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Overview and Outlook (Continued)</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Other Items</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">We generated $109.4 million in cash from operations during 2010, and we ended the year with $100.1 million in cash and cash equivalents.&#160;&#160;Our operating cash flow included an influx of approximately $42 million related to our 2009 federal income tax refund that we received in 2010.&#160;&#160;We did not make any federal income tax payments in 2010 and do not anticipate making federal income tax payments in 2011 due to the accelerated depreciation recognized for tax purposes related to our newly acquired CRJ-900 and Q400 aircraft. Operating cash flow was also improved in 2010 due to the acquisition of Mesaba, which contributed approximately $23 million in operating cash flow.&#160;&#160;Mesaba&#8217;s operating cash flow included a one-time benefit of approximately $14 million related to the establishment of our new CPAs with 
Delta.&#160;&#160;Our operating cash flow in 2011 will decline for several reasons, including the fact that we will not receive an income tax refund and because Mesaba&#8217;s operating cash flow will exclude the one-time benefit described above.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">We accepted delivery of eight Q400 aircraft in late 2010 and we will take delivery of an additional eight aircraft through August 2011 that will be operated under our capacity purchase agreement with United.&#160;&#160;We have a commitment from Export Development Canada (&#8220;EDC&#8221;) to finance 85% of the purchase price of each aircraft, and we expect to use our internally generated funds to pay for the remaining amount.&#160;&#160;We believe our current liquidity position and expected 2011 operating cash flow is sufficient to meet our remaining 2011 debt service requirements and the unfinanced portion of our Q400 purchase commitments.&#160;&#160;Under our capacity purchase agreement with United, payments associated with our capital investment in these aircraft are fixed over the ten-year term of the contract.&#160;&#160;We expe
ct that our Q400 growth will have a positive impact on operating income in 2011.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">In March 2011, we will begin operating seven leased Saab 340B+ aircraft within our pro-rate operations with scheduled service at New York&#8217;s LaGuardia airport as a US Airways Express carrier.&#160;&#160;This increase in service was driven by the delay in the transfer of the bulk of US Airways&#8217; regional takeoff and landing slots at LaGuardia to Delta (the &#8220;LaGuardia Slot Swap&#8221;).&#160;&#160;While we expect these operations to continue to at least the end of 2011, our agreement with US Airways is designed to be temporary and we will end service at LaGuardia upon any resolution of the LaGuardia Slot Swap between US Airways, Delta and the Department of Transportation.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">We continue to position ourselves to capitalize on long-term profitable opportunities to increase the number of regional aircraft that our subsidiaries operate.&#160;&#160;Our competitors&#8217; capacity purchase agreements for over 400 50-seat regional jet aircraft are set to expire between now and 2015.&#160;&#160;While many of these regional jets will likely no longer operate within the networks of the major U.S. airlines, we believe some of these contracts will be renewed or offered to other regional airlines and some will be replaced with larger regional jets.&#160;&#160;We intend to actively compete to obtain profitable regional jet and Q400 flying during this period of transition within the industry, and we believe our history of strong operating performance with a competitive cost structure will position us to succeed.&#160;&#
160;Our capacity purchase contracts do not begin to expire until December 2017.</font></div>

<br>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold"><a name="Item7resultsofops">Results of Operations</a></font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 36pt"></font>The following represents our results of operations, by segment and consolidated, for the year ended December 31, 2010.&#160;&#160;A discussion of our results of operations as compared to 2009 and 2008 follows.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">On December 17, 2010, the Company reached a tentative agreement with ALPA for a collective bargaining agreement covering pilots at Pinnacle, Mesaba, and Colgan.&#160;&#160;The agreement provided for a signing bonus of $10.1 million ($10.9 million inclusive of related payroll taxes) for Pinnacle&#8217;s pilots.&#160;&#160;This signing bonus, along with related employment taxes, was recorded as a charge to Pinnacle&#8217;s salaries, wages, and benefits expense in December 2010.&#160;&#160;On February 17, 2011, the pilots at Pinnacle, Mesaba, and Colgan ratified the contract.</font></div>

<br>
<div id="PGBRK" style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; WIDTH: 100%; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
<div id="FTR">
<div style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">&#160;</font></div>
</div>

<div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">&#160; </font></div>
</div>

<div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always; WIDTH: 100%">
<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: center; WIDTH: 100%"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">34</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: center; WIDTH: 100%">
<hr style="COLOR: black" noshade size="2">
</div>
</div>

<div id="HDR">
<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">&#160; </font></div>

<div style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Item 7.&#160;&#160;Management&#8217;s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations </font></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Results of Operations (Continued)</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Several nonrecurring items affected both operating and nonoperating expense in 2009.&#160;&#160;During 2009, we recorded a net increase to operating expense related to $2.0 million ($1.2 million net of tax) of return costs associated with the retirement of our Beech 1900 aircraft fleet, partially offset by the $0.8 million ($0.5 million net of tax) excess of insurance proceeds received over the cost basis of an aircraft that was destroyed.&#160;&#160;These items cumulatively reduced operating income by $1.2 million for the year ended December 31, 2009.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">During 2009, we recorded a net nonoperating gain of $3.9 million ($3.7 million net of tax) primarily related to the sale of our auction rate securities (&#8220;ARS&#8221;) portfolio.&#160;&#160;Our net income for 2009 also included net nonoperating gains of $0.2 million associated with the repurchase of certain indebtedness in the first quarter of 2009 and hedge losses associated with one Q400 aircraft that was destroyed.&#160;&#160;Our net income for the year ended December 31, 2009 was also increased by $15.4 million related to our settlement with the Internal Revenue Service on its examination of our federal tax returns for the tax years 2003 through 2005.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">During 2008, we recorded charges of $13.5 million ($8.7 million net of tax) related to the impairment of Colgan&#8217;s goodwill and certain charges necessary to retire several of Colgan&#8217;s aircraft associated with its pro-rate operations.&#160;&#160;In addition, during 2008, we recorded an impairment charge of $16.8 million ($16.1 million net of tax) to write down the value of our portfolio of auction rate securities to fair value.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Operating Revenues</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Operating revenue of $1.0 billion for the year ended December 31, 2010 increased $175.3 million, or 21%, compared to 2009.&#160;&#160;The increase in operating revenue was largely attributable to the acquisition of Mesaba, which contributed additional revenue of $141.4 million. The increase was also related to changes in our capacity purchase related operating revenue, primarily caused by changes in our operating fleet size, aircraft utilization, and changes in the costs that are directly reimbursed by our partners.&#160;&#160;In addition, changes in our pro-rate related operating revenue are primarily caused by changes in the scope of our pro-rate operations, and by the average load factor, average passenger fare, and average incentive payments we receive from our partners and under our Essential Air Service (&#8220;EAS&#8221;) agree
ments. &#160;(These changes are discussed in greater detail within our segmented results of operations.)</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Operating Expenses</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Operating expenses increased by $194.4 million, or 25%, as compared to 2009.&#160;&#160;This is primarily attributable to the acquisition of Mesaba, which contributed additional operating expenses of $134.5 million. (This change and others are discussed in greater detail within our segmented results of operations.)</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Nonoperating Expense</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Net nonoperating expense of $40.7 million for the year ended December 31, 2010 increased by approximately $2.2 million as compared to 2009.&#160;&#160;This increase is related to $3.9 million in interest expense on the Promissory Note,&#160;a decrease in interest income of $1.9 million due to the sale of our ARS portfolio in 2009, and a $1.7 million increase in nonoperating expense related to decreases in the fair value of our interest rate &#8220;Swaptions,&#8221; which are further discussed in Note 9, <font style="FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">Hedging Activities</font>, in Item 8 of this Form 10-K. &#160;In addition, we recorded net valuation gains of $1.8 million on our ARS call options for the year ended December 31, 2010 as compared to a $3.9 million net investment gain related to the sale of our ARS portfolio recorded i
n 2009.&#160;&#160;During the three months ended March 31, 2009, the Company recorded a gain of $1.9 million on the extinguishment of $12 million par amount of the Notes, partially offset by a $1.4 million charge for the previously unrecognized hedge related costs for the debt related to the aircraft destroyed in Flight 3407.&#160; Interest expense increased by $2.9 million related to the reversal of interest on income tax reserves during the three months ended March 31, 2009.&#160; Partially offsetting these increases was a $9.6 million decrease in interest expense related to the repurchase of our senior convertible notes in February 2010.&#160;</font></div>

<br>
<div id="PGBRK" style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; WIDTH: 100%; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
<div id="FTR">
<div style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block">&#160;</div>
</div>

<div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">&#160; </font></div>
</div>

<div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always; WIDTH: 100%">
<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: center; WIDTH: 100%"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">35</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: center; WIDTH: 100%">
<hr style="COLOR: black" noshade size="2">
</div>
</div>

<div id="HDR">
<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">&#160; </font></div>

<div style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Item 7.&#160;&#160;Management&#8217;s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations</font></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Results of Operations (Continued)</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Income Tax Expense</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">For the years ended December 31, 2010 and 2009, we recorded income tax expense of $8.1 million and $0.4 million, respectively.&#160;&#160;During 2009, we reached a settlement with the IRS regarding our examination for tax years 2003 through 2005. The Service had proposed a number of adjustments to our returns totaling approximately $35.0 million of additional tax, plus accrued interest and penalties on these proposed adjustments.&#160;&#160;The Company agreed to pay approximately $3.0 million of additional income tax and accrued interest in settlement of all open tax matters for the years examined.&#160;&#160;As a result, we recorded a reduction to income tax expense of $13.6 million in 2009 to reduce our accrued income tax reserves pursuant to the settlement.&#160;&#160;See Note 14, <font style="FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">I
ncome Taxes</font>, in Item 8 of this Form 10-K for more discussion.&#160;&#160;</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 1.4pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">2009 Compared to 2008</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Operating Revenues</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Operating revenue of $845.5 million for the year ended December 31, 2009 decreased $19.3 million, or 2%, compared to 2008.&#160;&#160;Changes in our capacity purchase related operating revenue are primarily caused by changes in our operating fleet size and aircraft utilization.&#160;&#160;Changes in our pro-rate related operating revenue are primarily caused by a reduction in the scope of our pro-rate operations that we undertook in the fall of 2008, and by changes in the average load factor, average passenger fare, and average incentive payments we receive from our partners and under our EAS agreements.&#160;&#160;These changes are discussed in greater detail within our segmented results of operations.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Operating Expenses</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Operating expenses decreased by $54.4 million, or 7%, as compared to 2008, primarily due to the decrease in fuel expense and gallons consumed at our Colgan subsidiary, along with the impairment of Colgan&#8217;s goodwill and other intangible assets during 2008.&#160;&#160;This change and others are discussed in greater detail within our segmented results of operations.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Nonoperating Expense</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Net nonoperating expense of $38.5 million for the year ended December 31, 2009 decreased by approximately $15.7 million as compared to 2008.&#160;&#160;The decrease is primarily related to the previously discussed $3.9 million net investment gain, as compared to the $16.8 million ARS impairment charge recorded during 2008.&#160;&#160;Interest expense increased slightly, primarily related to the addition of CRJ-900 and Q400 aircraft to our fleet throughout 2008, offset by the reversal of interest on tax reserves, as previously discussed, and by a reduction in interest expense on our senior convertible notes as a result of the repurchase and retirement of the majority of those obligations during 2009.&#160;&#160;The overall decrease was offset by a decrease in interest income of $4.9 million due to the decrease in interest rates on ou
r ARS portfolio, as well as the sale of our ARS portfolio in August 2009.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0.2pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Income Tax Expense</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">For the year ended December 31, 2009, we recorded income tax expense of $0.4 million.&#160;&#160;As previously discussed, in 2009 we reached settlement with the IRS regarding our examination for tax years 2003 through 2005. The IRS had proposed a number of adjustments to our returns totaling approximately $35.0 million of additional tax, plus accrued interest and penalties on these proposed adjustments.&#160;&#160;We agreed to pay approximately $3 million of additional income tax and accrued interest in settlement of all open tax matters for the years examined.&#160;&#160;As a result, we recorded a reduction to income tax expense of $13.6 million to reduce our accrued income tax reserves pursuant to the settlement.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Regional Airline Services</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><font style="FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">CRJ-200</font>.&#160; For the year ended December 31, 2010, revenue earned under our CRJ-200 ASA of $557.1 million increased by $16.2 million, or 3%.&#160;</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">For the year ended December 31, 2010, the rates that Delta pays us under our CRJ-200 ASA increased by 4%.&#160; Changes in our rates are tied to changes in the Producer Price Index, which increased by 4% from December 2008 to December 2009.&#160; This increase in rates caused an increase in our revenue of approximately $8.5 million.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Additionally, a change in reimbursable expenses caused revenue to increase by $9.7 million for the year ended December 31, 2010.&#160; For the year ended December 31, 2010, revenue from reimbursable expenses increased by $5.9 million related to heavy maintenance checks, $3.0 million for increased property taxes, $2.2 million related to increased insurance expenses, and $2.9 million in other reimbursable expenses.&#160; These increases were offset by a decrease of $4.3 million primarily related to reduced deicing expense, which is discussed further below.</font></div>

<br>
<div id="PGBRK" style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; WIDTH: 100%; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
<div id="FTR">
<div style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block">&#160;</div>
</div>

<div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">&#160; </font></div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: center; WIDTH: 100%"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">38</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-ALIGN: center; WIDTH: 100%">
<hr style="COLOR: black" noshade size="2">
</div>
</div>

<div id="HDR">
<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">&#160; </font></div>

<div style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Item 7.&#160;&#160;Management&#8217;s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations </font></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<br>
<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Results of Operations (Continued)</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">As a result of our amended CRJ-200 ASA, effective July 1, 2010, certain expenses changed classification to become pass&#8211;through expenses, while certain rates in the CRJ-200 ASA were reduced.&#160; These changes, along with a change in methodology related to departure based revenue, caused revenue for 2010 to decrease by approximately $2 million, as compared to 2009.&#160;</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">&#160;</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><font style="FONT-STYLE: italic; DISPLAY: inline">Pinnacle CRJ-900.&#160;&#160;</font>For the year ended December 31, 2010, revenue earned under the Pinnacle CRJ-900 DCA of $75.4 million increased by $7.2 million, or 11%, as compared to 2009.&#160;&#160;This increase is primarily related to an increase in the 2010 rates that Delta pays us under our Pinnacle CRJ-900 DCA, which resulted in an increase of revenue of approximately $4.6 million.&#160;&#160;In addition, revenue increased due to an increase in aircraft utilization, which caused block hours to increase by 2% and revenue to increase by approximately $0.2 million.&#160;&#160;The remaining increase is attributable to an increase in reimbursable expenses, which increased revenue by approximately $3.5 million.&#160;&#160;Offsetting this increase is a $1.1 million decrease in incen
tive revenue earned during the year ended December 31, 2010, primarily as a result of changes in our Pinnacle CRJ-900 DCA that became effective July 1, 2010.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Other Revenue</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Other revenue increased $6.7 million, or 76%, for the year ended December 31, 2010 as compared to 2009.&#160;&#160;This increase is related to an increase in third party ground handling revenue, as we are providing these services to other airlines in an increased number of cities.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">2009 Compared to 2008</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Regional Airline Services</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">For the year ended December 31, 2009, revenue earned under our CRJ-200 ASA of $540.9 million decreased by $28.1 million, or 5%, compared to 2008. Revenue earned under our CRJ-200 ASA was reduced by the return of 13 CRJ-200 aircraft throughout 2008 pursuant to the terms of our CRJ-200 ASA.&#160; During the year ended December 31, 2009, we operated 3% fewer average CRJ-200 aircraft than 2008.&#160; Compounding the reduction in our operating fleet size, we experienced declines in aircraft utilization.&#160; As a result of both the reduction in our CRJ-200 fleet size and the decline in aircraft utilization, volume based revenue decreased by $22.3 million, or 6%, during 2009, as compared to 2008.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">We recorded $8.9 million less in departure based revenue during 2009, as compared to 2008, as a result of a dispute with Delta over the amount that we earn for each departure under the CRJ-200 ASA.&#160;&#160;Delta asserted that it had the right under the CRJ-200 ASA to reduce both the revenue we receive and the cost we pay for ground handling services in certain cities where Delta or its designee provides ground handling services to us.&#160;&#160;During 2009, Delta began to compensate us according to its interpretation of the CRJ-200 ASA.&#160;&#160;As a result, the revenue we received for the year ended December 31, 2009, related to certain ground handling services was reduced by approximately $8.9 million, and our related ground handling costs were reduced by $8.1 million, with the resulting net effect of a reduction of operating 
income of approximately $0.8 million.&#160;</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Lastly, a change in other reimbursable expenses caused revenue to increase by $1.2 million, for the year ended December 31, 2009, as compared to 2008.&#160;&#160;Pursuant to the terms of our CRJ-200 ASA with Delta, we are reimbursed with margin for certain operational costs.&#160;&#160;These costs include certain maintenance costs, aircraft rentals, passenger liability and hull insurance, property taxes, fuel, ground handling at CRJ-200 ASA service cities, and landing fees at Detroit Metropolitan Wayne County Airport (&#8220;DTW&#8221;).&#160;&#160;To the extent that these reimbursable costs increase or decline, we experience a corresponding increase or decline in revenue.&#160;&#160;Revenue from reimbursable expenses increased by $5.8 million related to heavy maintenance checks, $1.6 million related to increased deicing expense, $3.8
 million related to increased insurance expenses, and $0.6 million related to other maintenance expense.&#160;&#160;These increases were offset by a decrease of $4.1 million related to reduced property taxes, $2.6 million related to reduced engine maintenance expense, and $3.9 million related to reduced aircraft rental expense.</font></div>

<br>
